HEADWORD: Ductility
<hw>Duc*til"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ductilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The property of a
metal which allows it to be drawn into wires or filaments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tractableness; pliableness.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duction</ent>⟦br⟧
